quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  16,84,Do they realize what will happen on that Day when We shall call a witness from every nation? Then the unbelievers will neither be allowed to put forward any excuse nor will they receive any favor
  16,85,"When the wrongdoers face the punishment, it will neither be lightened for them nor will they be granted a delay"
  16,86,"When the pagans see their deities whom they associated with Allah, they will say: \"Our Lord! Here are our ‘associate gods’ whom we used to invoke besides You.\" At this their deities will toss their statement back at them saying: \"You are liars"
  16,87,"They shall tender their submission to Allah that Day: and the gods of their own inventions will leave them in the lurch"
  16,88,"As for those who disbelieve and debar others from the Way of Allah, We shall punish them all the more for their misdeeds"
  16,89,"O Muhammad, warn them about that Day when We shall call a witness from every nation to testify against it, and We shall call you O Muhammad to testify against your people: that is why We have sent down to you this Book (The Qur'an) to explain everything - a guide, a blessing and good news for Muslims"